## Why this is correct

The entire coordinate problem solved in one place:

```
ARCore camera image → YUV → Bitmap (landscape, 90° rotated)
        ↓
rotateBitmap 90° → upright portrait bitmap
        ↓
ML Kit sees upright bitmap, rotation=0
        ↓
ML Kit bounding boxes are in upright portrait pixel coords
        ↓
Scale to screen: screenX = boxX * (screenW / uprightW)
                 screenY = boxY * (screenH / uprightH)
        ↓
ARCore hit-test at those screen coords → lands exactly on text
```

No PixelCopy. No CameraX. No coordinate transforms beyond one simple scale. ARCore gives us the frame, we rotate it once, ML Kit reads it upright, boxes map directly to screen with a scale factor.